  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, former Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte and former U.S. President Donald Trump had shown a mutual rapport during their time in office or afterwards. Duterte has publicly expressed admiration for Trump, often praising his leadership style and policies. For instance, Duterte has commended Trump's approach to foreign policy and his willingness to deal with him directly and pragmatically, particularly on issues like counterterrorism and the U.S.-Philippines alliance.\n\nDuterte, known for his blunt and often controversial rhetoric, has also appreciated Trump's similarly straightforward communication style, often contrasting it with other Western leaders. Trump, in return, has largely avoided criticizing Duterte, even when the latter's human rights record and anti-drug campaign were under international scrutiny.\n\nHowever, the relationship between the two leaders was largely transactional and focused on mutual interests rather than deep ideological alignment. For the most accurate and recent developments, refer to up-to-date news sources.",
